# AgToosa Ship Rules

When executing `/agtoosa-ship` or any shipping work, follow `Docs/AgToosa_Ship.md` precisely.

## Key constraints

- `/agtoosa-ship check` is a read-only Part 0 readiness audit — no deployment, archive, or file mutation.
- Full `/agtoosa-ship` requires Part 0 to pass before deployment begins (no 🔴 Critical findings; story approved in Master-Plan and review archive).
- Zero-downtime deployment strategy is required — verify rollback plan exists before deploying. Deploy only via a documented target in `Docs/Context/tech-stack.md`; otherwise mark deployment `[manual]`.
- Verify `Docs/archived/spec-[story-id].md` and `review-[story-id].md` exist; do **not** rename archived files on ship.
- Update `Docs/AgToosa_Changelog.md` and `Docs/Master-Plan.md` after a successful ship.
- Always end with a retro summary and a suggested next story.
- On successful completion, print this line verbatim: `Next: /agtoosa-<command> — <rationale>` plus `SYNC:` pulse (see Lifecycle Next-Step Contract)
